reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect solution for your Hp
reviews.reviewText: No upgrade would be possible. Allows the ease of upgrading to a bigger power supply and case

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The cord is better quality and better price than the others, and works great in my PC. The larger motherboard plugin has two sections, one being a 4-pin, that’s a bit difficult to slide onto the other piece because you have to pull on the cords a bit to do it, so be careful. It did come with the little black wire for the F1 “Power supply fan not detected” error, but I still get the error every time I boot up my HP Elite 8100. It might be better in an 8200/8300. Still, it didn’t set my PC on fire like I’ve read about in reviews for other versions of this cord by other brands, nor did it short circuit my hardware. If not for the fan error, I’d give this five stars!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far so good!
reviews.reviewText: I have a hp prodesk 600 G1 and was struggling to find the right psu adapter. This one almost gave me the blues again but after about 10 seconds my pc started up! I'm running a 800w psu for a rx 580 on a i7 4770. Only boot up problem is because I unplugged the front USB from the motherboard to fit the rx 580

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Does not work
reviews.reviewText: Does not work with HP ProDesk 600 G1 SFF. Blinking green light. I'm now 0 for 3 on these adapters. Three strikes, I'm out. I give up. Just these adapters alone made it not even worth the cost to do a case-swap at this point. It's a shame there's so many of these adapters being falsely advertised as compatible.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works as hoped
reviews.reviewText: I have an older HP that I wanted to upgrade the power supply, and needed an adapter for the motherboard. This worked perfectly and I haven’t had any issues so far. The only reason this isn’t 5 stars is the cap colors don’t match the original power supply cables, so make sure to pay close attention to which one goes where when you install. Also the length of a couple cables made for a stretch to get it connected, but no strain I can see on the cabling.
